Street, Kent, England","England":"England","Kent, England":"Kent, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"d'Arderne","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Patrice, Jacques.","French and Walloon: habitational name, with fused preposition <i>d(e)</i> ‘from’, for someone from the Ardennes, a forested plateau in northeastern France, Belgium (Wallonia), and Luxembourg.","French: habitational name, with fused preposition <i>d(e)</i> ‘from’, for someone from a place called Ardenne, for example in Charente-Maritime and Haute-Loire."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":67,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Alice d'Arderne was born in Faversham, Kent, England as the daughter of John Baker and Isabella. She married Sir Simon Baker 1st about 1453, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1506, in her hometown."},"et":{"–1506":"–1506","1400–1484":"1400–1484","–Male":"Surnud","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1425–1491":"1425–1491","–Female":"Surnud","1425":"1425","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1420":"1420","1484":"1484","about 1453":"umbes 1453","1470":"1470","1491":"1491","1506":"1506","Faversham, Kent, England":"Faversham, Kent, England","Sissinghurst, Kent, England":"Milkhouse Street, Kent, England","England":"England","Kent, England":"Kent, England"},"fi":{"–1506":"–1506","1400–1484":"1400–1484","–Male":"Kuollut","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1425–1491":"1425–1491","–Female":"Kuollut","1425":"1425","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1420":"1420","1484":"1484","about 1453":"noin 1453","1470":"1470","1491":"1491","1506":"1506","Faversham, Kent, England":"Faversham, Kent, England","Sissinghurst, Kent, England":"Milkhouse Street, Kent, England","England":"England","Kent, England":"Kent, England"},"fr":{"–1506":"–1506","1400–1484":"1400–1484","–Male":"Décédé","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1425–1491":"1425–1491","–Female":"Décédée","1425":"1425","1455":"1455","1400":"1400","1420":"1420","1484":"1484","about 1453":"environ 1453","1470":"1470","1491":"1491","1506":"1506","Faversham, Kent, England":"Faversham, Kent, Angleterre","Sissinghurst, Kent, England":"Milkhouse Street, Kent, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","Kent, England":"Kent, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Alice d'Arderne est née à Faversham, Kent, Angleterre, fille de John Baker et Isabella. Elle a épousé Sir Simon Baker 1st environ 1453, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille. Elle est décédée en 1506, dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"–1506":"–1506","1400–1484":"1400–1484","–Male":"Verstorben","1420–1470":"1420–1470","1425–1491":"1